-- Fast install for Raspberry PI (raspbian) --

This install assumes that the current directory is where this file is located.

There are a few dependencies that must be checked before compiling imgv.
Some dependencies are packages, some are actual code you must compile.
The full instructions for dependencies are in the file other/README.

Execute theses commands:

---
sudo apt-get install build-essential cmake-curses-gui libopencv-dev libpng12-dev
sudo apt-get install libavutil-dev libavformat-dev libavcodec-dev libswscale-dev
sudo apt-get install libav-tools doxygen
sudo apt-get install libglew-dev


-- read this:  /opt/vc/src/hello_pi/README 
cd /opt/vc/src/hello_pi/libs/ilclient
make
(that's it)

-- glfw
sudo apt-get install libgegl-dev x11proto-xf86vidmode-dev libxxf86vm-dev
cd other/glfw-3.0.1 && mkdir -p build && cd build
ccmake ..

	GLFW_BUILD_EXAMPLES	OFF
	GLFW_USE_EGL		ON
[c]
	GLFW_CLIENT_LIBRARY	glesv2
[c]
	EGL_INCLUDE_DIR		/opt/vc/include
	EGL_LIBRARY		/opt/vc/lib/libEGL.so
[c]
	GLESv2_INCLUDE_DIR	/usr/include/gegl-0.2 ; /opt/vc/include ; /opt/vc/include/interface/vcos/pthreads
	GLESv2_LIBRARY		/usr/lib/arm-linux-gnueabihf/libgegl-0.2.so

make && sudo make install

---- raspicam ----

http://www.uco.es/investiga/grupos/ava/node/40
http://sourceforge.net/projects/raspicam/files/

# for example:
http://sourceforge.net/projects/raspicam/files/raspicam-0.1.3.zip/download

cd raspicam-0.1.3
mkdir build
cd build
cmake ..
make
sudo make install

--- oscpack

cd other/oscpack_1_1_0 && mkdir -p build && cd build && cmake .. && make && sudo make install && cd ../../..

echo "export LD_LIBRARY_PATH=\${LD_LIBRARY_PATH}:/usr/local/lib" >> ~/.bashrc
---

At this point, make sure you exit and restart a new terminal, so the new installed libraries are seen by bash. Go to the imgv directory containing this file.

Then execute these commands:

--
mkdir -p build && cd build && cmake .. && make && sudo make install
--

To test, just execute:

playImage

The indian head should show up. Move the mouse over the image and press 1,2,3,4 to distort the image.

The documentation will be installed here:

file:///usr/local/share/imgv/docs/html/index.html

That's it!

